<i>motorway...</i>

00:39.122 --> 00:41.124
<i>excursion...</i>

00:42.292 --> 00:44.044
<i>and carbine.</i>

00:47.589 --> 00:53.095
<i>A sea is a leather armchair 
with wooden arms</i>

00:53.303 --> 00:55.806
<i>like the one we have
in our living room.</i>

00:56.765 --> 01:01.311
<i>For example:
Don't stand on your feet.</i>

01:01.562 --> 01:05.147
<i>Sit on the sea to have
a quiet chat with me.</i>

01:06.566 --> 01:11.822
<i>A motorway is a very strong wind.</i>

01:14.825 --> 01:20.455
<i>An excursion is a very resistant material...</i>

01:20.664 --> 01:23.500
<i>used to construct floors.</i>

01:24.459 --> 01:25.961
<i>For example:</i>

01:26.503 --> 01:30.132
<i>The chandelier fell violently 
onto the floor...</i>

01:30.340 --> 01:32.968
<i>but no damage was caused to it...</i>

01:33.176 --> 01:36.805
<i>because it is made of 100% excursion.</i>

01:40.475 --> 01:41.768
<i>Carbine.</i>

01:42.644 --> 01:47.316
<i>A carbine is a beautiful white bird.</i>

01:53.697 --> 01:58.368
I say we play a game of endurance.

01:59.870 --> 02:04.041
By that I mean we run hot water
from the taps...

02:04.666 --> 02:07.502
place a finger under the water...

02:07.961 --> 02:11.798
and the one who lasts longest wins.

02:14.217 --> 02:15.469
What do you think?

02:18.138 --> 02:20.015
I like it.

02:21.391 --> 02:23.352
- You?
- I like it as well.

02:24.061 --> 02:27.022
Shall we use all the taps or just one?

02:27.230 --> 02:29.733
We'll just use one if you like.

02:30.233 --> 02:31.860
How will we time it?

02:32.069 --> 02:36.073
With a clock or a stopwatch?

02:36.323 --> 02:39.743
No need.
We'll put our fingers in together.

02:39.993 --> 02:43.205
Last one to take their finger out wins.

02:44.247 --> 02:47.834
So we need all three taps running?

02:49.086 --> 02:52.255
We could do it with just one.

02:52.506 --> 02:56.593
If we use three, someone might sneak
their finger out for a moment.

02:56.843 --> 03:01.264
We could use the bathtub.
It's bigger.

03:03.392 --> 03:05.560
What should we call this game?

03:16.697 --> 03:18.115
I don't know...

03:27.124 --> 03:30.585
Do you like the music
or should I put something else on?

03:31.962 --> 03:33.755
No, it's okay.

03:34.923 --> 03:38.719
No need to be shy.
If you don't like it, let me know.

03:40.137 --> 03:41.805
No, I do like it.

03:42.639 --> 03:44.725
What's your favorite song?

03:49.896 --> 03:51.148
I have two.

04:00.323 --> 04:01.950
Have you taken a bath?

04:03.827 --> 04:04.619
Yes.

04:04.828 --> 04:06.621
Did you wash your hair?

04:09.291 --> 04:12.002
Not my hair.
I washed it yesterday.

05:09.726 --> 05:12.562
- Do you feel dizzy?
- No, I'm fine.

05:33.583 --> 05:34.709
Are you done?

05:36.586 --> 05:38.547
Christina is here.

08:07.153 --> 08:09.698
- Hello, Christina.
- Hello.

08:12.367 --> 08:13.743
You've lost weight.

08:15.078 --> 08:16.246
Yes, a little.

08:17.080 --> 08:19.332
Can I stay, or am I disturbing you?

08:19.749 --> 08:22.919
Stay. You're not disturbing me in the least.

08:33.722 --> 08:36.057
What are those things on your headband?

08:36.683 --> 08:38.934
Sparkling stones.

08:39.561 --> 08:40.937
Sparkling?

08:41.604 --> 08:44.441
They shine in the dark,
like little lights.

08:45.775 --> 08:48.027
Without any power?

08:48.236 --> 08:49.362
Sure.

08:50.780 --> 08:52.532
You're lying.

08:52.741 --> 08:54.367
No, I'm not.

08:55.618 --> 08:57.454
Where did you get it?

08:58.621 --> 09:00.457
I made it myself.

09:01.291 --> 09:02.375
Well done.

09:03.084 --> 09:04.127
Thanks.

09:06.546 --> 09:07.922
Do you have a headband?

09:08.131 --> 09:11.134
A brown one.
But I gave it to my little sister.

09:11.384 --> 09:15.138
She gave me a pair of socks
and two big rubber erasers.

09:15.388 --> 09:17.640
Are those the socks?

09:17.807 --> 09:19.893
No, another pair.

09:21.436 --> 09:23.313
They're nice too.

09:23.563 --> 09:24.606
Thanks.

09:29.277 --> 09:31.321
Will you join us for dinner?

09:32.155 --> 09:34.324
No, unfortunately I have to go.

09:34.991 --> 09:37.619
Too bad. We're having burgers.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.663
Burgers are one of my favorite meals.

09:44.417 --> 09:46.086
What are the others?

09:48.838 --> 09:51.174
I like fish soup and cheese pie.

09:51.341 --> 09:53.843
Fish soup and cheese pie are perfect.

09:54.177 --> 09:56.930
- I had fish soup yesterday.
- Lovely.

10:09.859 --> 10:12.779
There's apple in the juice too.

10:12.987 --> 10:14.364
It's very tasty.

10:19.702 --> 10:21.120
Unfortunately, I have to go.

10:21.871 --> 10:23.832
Shall I shoot a video
with all of us?

10:24.040 --> 10:26.876
Go ahead, we don't have
a video with Christina.

10:27.126 --> 10:29.712
Do you mind if we film us all together?

10:29.879 --> 10:31.172
Not at all.

10:44.561 --> 10:48.231
- Dad, can I sit next to Christina?
- Yes, honey.

10:56.739 --> 10:59.868
Christina, can you smile a bit more?

